
Ranger Help for: setsecond
==========================

SYNTAX:      setsecond/setsecond <your secondary terrain name here>
USAGE:       Any wilderness terrain/one time use.

SUMMARY:    
Allows the Ranger to set his or her secondary terrain. THIS COMMAND MAY
ONLY BE USED ONCE. Available terrains are: 

         forest  plains  swamp  desert  jungle  hills
         beach   arctic  barren underground  mountain 

A Ranger's secondary terrain is the terrain in which the he/she spent some
time in growing up. But the Ranger doesn't know it as well as they're
primary terrain. A Ranger's secondary terrain will affecT the same kinds
of things as their primary terrain, just not as much. 

In combat, secondary terrain still matters. A Ranger fighting there
currently receives +10 dodge and roughly +10% damage. It is not as strong
as primary terrain, but it is still a meaningful edge over unfavored
ground.

Choose your secondary terrain carefully, for it is a one time command. Use
'rhelp <terrain>' to read about each terrain before choosing.

NOTE: Primary and secondary terrains can be the same.

=============================================================================
SEE ALSO: setprime, setenemy, terrains, survey and followers
